==English==

===Etymology===
From "Silicon Valley USA", the title of a series of articles appearing in 1971 in ''[[w:Electronic News|Electronic News]]'' by the journalist [[w:Don Hoefler|Don Hoefler]], from '''[[silicon]]''', the element used by these industries + '''[[valley]]''' from [[w:Santa Clara Valley|Santa Clara Valley]], the area where many of these industries are located

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[silicon|Silicon]] [[valley|Valley]]'''

#A [[nickname]] originally for the region of [[San Francisco]] in which there are a high number of industries producing [[silicon chip]]s and later extended to mean the entire concentration of [[high-tech]] businesses in this area.

